\centerline{\includegraphics[width=0.9\textwidth]{img/Stokes_v2.pdf}}
\caption{\textbf{Uncertainty guided nomination in virtual screens.} \textbf{(A)} Experimental framework in which trained uncertainty-aware models are deployed on a discovery dataset, and molecules are ranked based on predicted properties. Uncertainty filtering is used to prioritize candidates among the top ranking molecules. \textbf{(B)} Performance of evidential D-MPNN after training to predict \textit{E. coli} growth inhibition. \textbf{(C)} t-SNE visualization of training set (orange) and discovery dataset (Broad library), colored by predicted evidential uncertainties (blue). \textbf{(D)} Application of confidence filters to prioritize sets of antibiotic candidates with high experimental hit rates. Mean $\pm$ $95\%$ c.i., $n=10$ independent trials.}
\label{fig:stokes}
