To visualize the set of molecules acquired during the Bayesian optimization routine, we projected the 2048-bit atom-pair fingerprints of the Enamine HTS library into two dimensions using UMAP\cite{mcinnes_umap_2020} (Figures~\ref{fig:umap} and \ref{fig:umap_si}). The embedding of the library was trained on a random 10\% subset of the full library and then applied to the full library. Comparing the location of the top-1000 molecules (Figure~\ref{fig:umap}A) to the density of molecules in the entire 2M library (Figure~\ref{fig:umap}B) reveals several regions of high-performing compounds located in sparse regions of library chemical space, of which we focus on three (black ellipses). %
